description: Test the mechanical operation and electrical continuity of the relay in the control module by manually actuating (if possible) and measuring for contact bounce or instability when the relay changes state. This includes checking for contact bounce or chatter using an oscilloscope or similar tool., outcome='The inspection panel was opened successfully, and the control relay was visually inspected with no observable internal faults. Continuity testing of the control relay showed nominal resistance (0.01 Ω), indicating expected electrical continuity. Note: Simulation indicated an unstable or oscillating circuit state.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=35.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power supply module output cables,
description: Test the voltage at the power supply module output cables to verify stable 12V supply and exclude transient supply instability as a contributing factor to the oscillation., outcome="The measured voltage at 'PSU Output Cable (+)' is approximately 11.87 V, while at 'PSU Output Cable (−)' it is near 0 V with a small offset (0.0115 V). No polarity inversion is detected between the PSU output cables; the readings indicate expected polarity.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
