description: Test the electrical continuity of the potentiometer wiper connections to the comparator in the control module, as simulation indicates wiper ports are disconnected. Verify wiring continuity from potentiometer wipers to the relevant comparator circuit points to check for loose or broken connections., outcome='Diagnostic result: Continuity measurements show that both the sensitivity potentiometer and timing potentiometer wiper connections to the control relay are shorted; both are on the same circuit node (net_5) with 0.0 Ω resistance. No polarity inversion is indicated in the test results. Simulation did not converge and the circuit is unstable or oscillating.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=75.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
